  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0b95\u0bcb\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bbe\u0baa\u0bbe\u0baf \u0bb5\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0b95\u0bbf\u0baf \u0baa\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0ba9\u0bb0\u0bcd\u2026? \u0b85\u0bb0\u0b9a\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bb2\u0bae\u0bc8\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1 \u0b95\u0bc2\u0bb1\u0bc1\u0bb5\u0ba4\u0bc1 \u0b87\u0ba4\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bbe\u0ba9\u0bcd !",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "After Gotabaya left...? This is what the constitution says!",
      "author": "Vishnu",
      "body_lines": [
        "President Gotabaya Rajapaksa has announced that he will resign from his post on the 13th.",
        "He became the President on November 18, 2019 and now his term of office has completed 2 years and 7 months.",
        "Article 40 of the 1978 Constitution states that if a President resigns before the completion of his term, what is the next procedure.",
        "Accordingly, when a popularly elected President becomes vacant before the end of the term, a special procedure as laid down in Article 40 must be followed.",
        "Accordingly, to fill the vacancy of the President, the Parliament shall elect one of its members as the President within one month of the resignation of the President.",
        "At the same time, if the President resigns, Parliament must meet within three days of the President's resignation.",
        "At such meeting, the Secretary-General of Parliament shall inform Parliament of the resignation of the President and fix a date for receiving nominations for the vacant post of President.",
        "If only one Member of Parliament is nominated for the office of President, that person is declared elected to that office by the Secretary-General.",
        "If more than one person is nominated, a secret ballot shall be held and the election shall be by an absolute majority.",
        "Meanwhile, the Presidential Elections (Special Provisions) Act No. 2 of 1981 specifies the procedures to be followed by Parliament in electing a new President.",
        "Accordingly, during the period between the office of the President becoming vacant and the inauguration of a new President, the incumbent Prime Minister acts as Acting President.",
        "During this period, one of the Ministers of the Cabinet will be appointed to act in the Office of the Prime Minister. The newly elected president can remain in office for the remainder of the term.",
        "In such a situation, if President Gotabaya resigns from his position, Ranil Wickremesinghe will take over as the interim president until the parliament elects a new president within a month.",
        "All parties, including party leaders, are pressuring Prime Minister Ranil Wickremesinghe to resign. After the resignation of the President, if Prime Minister Ranil Wickremesinghe also resigns, the current Speaker Mahinda Yappa Abeywardhana will be elected as the President.",
        "Provisions for this are found in the constitution. However, if an all-party interim government is to be formed, Prime Minister Ranil Wickremesinghe will be eligible to assume the duties of interim president if he does not step down until that government is formed."
      ],
